Defendant Roman D Lovelace in court with attorney Parker Charles Mathers.  Defendant Roman D Lovelace in custody.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for sentencing hearing. Parties are prepared to proceed. Statements made as to sentencing. Court finds the State has complied with the victim rights legislation.

As to COUNT 1-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 5 YEARS, consecutive to COUNT 2, with credit for 153 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 3 YEARS.  

As to COUNT 2-
The Court sentenced the defendant to 6 MONTHS incarceration, consecutive to COUNT 1.

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program ONLY if he has not participated in the program before. The defendant is NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

Court costs, fees, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds/earnings.

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
1) Pay restitution in the amount of $208.41 to be paid to Jacqueline G. Restitution to be paid FIRST before costs, fees and surcharges;
2) Pay all costs, fees, surcharges and restitution. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
3) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge on COUNT 1 only. Court WAIVED DNA surcharge on COUNT 2 as it is part of a continuous course of conduct;
4) No contact with the victim or the co-defendant;
5) Maintain absolute sobriety from all illegal substances;
6) Random urine screens;
7) Maintain full time employment of at least 40 hours per week, or vocational/educational programming, or a combination of both;

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
